  "texts": [
    "For the SWMH dataset, RoBERTa-base 30 was identified as the best model in the paper, therefore we adopted RoBERTa as the pre-trained embedding layers for our architecture.",
    "RoBERTa is similar to the BERT model in architecture and training objectives but differs in that it is trained on a larger corpus and with longer sequences, which results in improved performance on a wide range of natural language processing tasks.",
    "Regarding the PsySym dataset, our initial choice was BERT-base-uncased, in line with established baseline reports.",
    "However, combining modeling tasks exacerbates data scarcity, particularly when there is not a substantially balanced ratio of patients with multiple mental conditions.",
    "Consequently, we encountered challenges in training models with meaningful predictive capabilities using similar settings (e.g., learning rates and other hyperparameters) without resorting to more advanced techniques and dataset manipulations."
  ],
